subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of dentition based on eight C&S specimens. Premaxillary teeth in two distinct rows. Outer row teeth 2-3 (mode = 2, n = 8), tricuspid. Inner row teeth 3-6 (mode 5, n = 8), tricuspid. Maxillary teeth 4-6 (mode = 5, n = 8), all conic or anterior 1-3 teeth tricuspid and all 2-5 posterior teeth conic. Dentary teeth 10-13 (mode 12, n = 8) in single row with anterior 3-4 teeth largest and tricuspid and followed posteriorly by 7-9 tricuspid to conic teeth gradually diminishing in size posteriorly. Central cusp of premaxillary, maxillary, and dentary teeth larger than lateral cusps (
Fig. 6
).
